definitions.definition: To print over what has already been printed.
To add an overprint to (a stamp).
To print too many copies of.
examples: The unpopular comic book was overprinted , leaving many retailers with dozens of unsaleable copies.

definitions.definition: To overlap different colours to avoid gaps.

To superimpose a new set of petrological , structural , and/or mineralogical characteristics onto rock by the action of geological processes over deep time , by analogy with the original sense of the word.

main_definition: To print over what has already been printed.
